 * `runInInitialEmptyDocument` boolean (optional) - Whether to run this frame
   preload in an iframe's initial empty document before its real navigation
   commits. This is only supported when `type` is `frame`. Defaults to `false`.
+* `target` string (optional) - Service worker target where the preload script
+  will be executed. Can be `shadow-realm-global-scope`,
+  `service-worker-global-scope` or `both`. This is only supported when `type` is
+  `service-worker`. Defaults to `shadow-realm-global-scope` to preserve
+  Electron's existing isolated service worker preload behavior. Use
+  `service-worker-global-scope` to run in the actual `ServiceWorkerGlobalScope`,
+  where worker Web APIs such as `navigator` are available. Use `both` to run the
+  preload in both global scopes; the script will execute twice.
 * `id` string (optional) - Unique ID of preload script. Defaults to a random UUID.
 * `filePath` string - Path of the script file. Must be an absolute path.
